Lyrics:
"My candle burns at both ends;
 They say it will not last the night;
 But ah, my foes, and oh, my friends
 My candle gives a lovely light!"

 How is any person ever
 Supposed to make amends
 For all the damage that he's done
 By burning his candle at both ends 

 Once we burned so bright together
 And though we did cast a lovely light 
 Now I can only say that I’m sorry 
 That my candle did not last the night 

 I burned my candle at both ends;
 Just like they said, it did not last the night;
 But ah, my foes, and oh, my friends
 I only meant to cast a lovely light!

